p: There were significant differences in the percentage of fed insects between control and citronellic acid (65 versus 36.7%, χ 2 = 4.73, p = 0.03). No significant differences were found between control and geraniol (80 versus 58.3%, χ 2 = 2.03, p = 0.154), control and eugenol (80 versus 65%, χ 2 = 0.93, p = 0.335), and between control and carvacrol (65 versus 48.3%, χ 2 = 1.47, p = 0.225).
